cs.CR, cs.SE, cs.AR, cs.SY, cs.PL 

The paper discusses a hardware-based bug that allows an attacker to modify data in memory, which is a security issue. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also proposes a framework for analyzing rowhammer attacks, which involves software engineering (cs.SE) and computer architecture (cs.AR). The paper also discusses countermeasures, which involves system design (cs.SY) and programming languages (cs.PL).
